name: intersection
signature: { <A>(that: Iterable<A>): (self: HashSet<A>) => HashSet<A>; <A>(self: HashSet<A>, that: Iterable<A>): HashSet<A>; }
description:
Returns a `HashSet` of values which are present in both this set and that
`Iterable<A>`. Computes set intersection (A ∩ B) Time complexity: `O(n)` where n is the number of elements in the smaller
set
*NOTE: the hash and equal of the values in both the set and the iterable
must be the same.
